Record Class CafeteriaDTO

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.cafe.backend.dto.CafeteriaDTO
Record Components:
id - The unique identifier of the cafeteria. Should be null when creating a new cafeteria.
name - The name of the cafeteria (required).
brand - The brand or franchise name of the cafeteria (required).
location - The physical location/address of the cafeteria (required).
rating - The average rating of the cafeteria, initialized to 0.0 when created.
countReview - The number of reviews submitted for the cafeteria, typically 0 at creation.
phoneNumber - The phone number for contacting the cafeteria (required).
openingHour - The opening hour of the cafeteria, formatted as H:mm.
closingHour - The closing hour of the cafeteria, formatted as H:mm.
imageUrl - A link to an image representing the cafeteria (optional).
public record CafeteriaDTO(Long id, String name, String brand, String location, double rating, int countReview, String phoneNumber, LocalTime openingHour, LocalTime closingHour, String imageUrl) extends Record
The CafeteriaDTO is a Data Transfer Object used to encapsulate data related to a cafeteria entity for both input (creation/update) and output (response).

This record is designed to be immutable and is annotated with @Builder to support fluent object creation using the builder pattern.

Fields such as name, brand, location, and phoneNumber are required for creation. The fields rating and countReview are typically initialized to default values (e.g., 0.0, 0) upon creation.

The openingHour and closingHour fields are formatted using the H:mm pattern for 24-hour time representation.
